                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">police-constable H</hi> 122.) On the afternoon of the 23rd of Nov., about half-past five o'clock, I saw the prisoner and two others in Hackney-road, at the shop of Mr. West, a linen-draper, looking in at the window—I then saw the prisoner take a roll of canvas from outside the shop door—he carried it seven or eight feet—one of his companions gave a sort of</p>
